A truck driver has died and a passenger seriously injured after their vehicle went down the Van Rhyn Mountain Pass. CAPE TOWN - A truck driver has died and a passenger seriously injured after their vehicle went down the Van Rhyn Mountain Pass. In another accident, a motorist was killed and another was seriously injured during a head-on collision on the N2 highway near Caledon on WednesdayThursday afternoon.Western Cape traffic chief Kenny Africa has more details about a third accident. Earlier on Wednesday, there was an accident outside Beaufort West where a driver lost control of his vehicle. One person was killed. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)